 documents this explicitly:\n\n> `gwc` is **not** a replacement for `git`. It only adds opinionated shortcuts on top of an existing local repository. Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\n\n`gwc` is designed to complement `git` for a few specific local workflows — branch name generation, status summaries, and cleaning merged branches — not to be a full git wrapper.\n\nFor pushing, please use `git push` directly. Hope that clarifies things!"}, "id": "call_1ffd510539d74c7da5d1dacc", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8610, "output_tokens": 683, "total_tokens": 9293, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7936}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 288}}}}]}}}
